<br>
"Howdy folks, <br>
<br>
This will indeed be a change that makes it to the Live servers, during our next scheduled update on September 14th. <br>
<br>
We feel that the current implimentation of AE kiting gave bards an unfair advantage in experience gain. It is our opinion that the changes currently on test will resolve this issue, while retaining both the Bards solo abilities and raid utility. <br>
<br>
Sorry folks but no more kiting 20 mobs at a time. <br>
<br>
Brenlo"<br>
<br>
My response, and much more eloquent and much less than the two taps behind the ear the SoE staff so richly deserve. Yeah, I'm that pissed. Over a stupid game nonetheless.<br>
<br>
Brenlo/SoE,<br>
Yet again you have taken something away from bards, and 33.3% of our abilty to play the game at our leisure, without requiring the time sink that is a group, when we realistically due to RL reasons, cannot commit that time, or choose to. Bards have 3, yes 3, ways of soloing anything of worthwhile xp content. AE, charm, and chant. At the level SoE must cater to, where 2/3+ of its playerbase lie.<br>
Our chants have been aggro nerfed.<br>
Our new charm is useless at level 70 to solo, intentionally, and barely of use, in limited, very limited zones currently.<br>
Our AE has now been nerfed to the point of uselessness.<br>
You say that this will not affect Bards raiding and grouping abilities-<br>
You lie, like you always have, and you are wrong.<br>
Bye bye a Bards usefuleness in AE groups-<br>
Bye bye a bards usefulness in AE encounters at the upper level. AE songs are now nerfed to melee range in xp zones.<br>
<br>
Bye bye the small percentage of bards who truly ENJOY this method at 65, your largest playerbase, and to be honest, your real paying customer. <br>
Hello to the path of least resistance, the easiest way to code things, take an abilty ENTIRELY from a Bard spellbook.<br>
 And say Hi to the fact that there are so MANY other fixes to this micro problem Sony perceives, that they take it over the 160 other issues that have been addressed on the class boards, and decide to swing the bat at this.<br>
<br>
We pay our money SoE, why don't you take the time to fix it RIGHT. I and many many others would pay a hell of alot more to see things done CORRECTLY.THis board is full of things being done WRONG. Is it a matter of money? Ask any class on any board. Charge me another 5 bucks, and fix things RIGHT.<br>
<br>
A total of 7 zones in the game would need the same fix that HoH has already had. Nadox, LoIO, Dulak, PoN, PoV, Freeport and Iceclad.<br>
Yet you choose not to.<br>
Has to be money, no other reason makes a bit of sense, and SO many other fixes available.<br>
AE songs use mana.<br>
Upgrade the level songs can be used at to a non PL level, like 55+ 60+. Most classes PL better than we do, but if thats the problem, there is a solution.<br>
The HoH fix as has been mentioned.<br>
This issue has been addressed once with the EN nerf, and you lost approximately half of the Bard playerbase since then. <br>
Don't you get it, why does the extinction of  the Bard class need to continue on the raid, AND the solo level?<br>
Perhaps we are an inconvenience to SoE, the unwelcome child of Verant, who like a sister in-laws children, must be endured till summer camp ?<br>
Welcome to OoW, of which GoD is the first part of. These boards are deluged with the problems GoD has for Bards. Due to previous perfomance being proof of future expectations, I truly have a hard time believing that anything less than the utter uselessness of our class will be in store in the future. I had hope for the beta, but am sure that this is only placebo. Bards just do not fit into the 'vision' SoE has. My proof? No Bards in EQ2<br>
<br>
Why do you feel the need to yet again mess with the least played class of the game? We are undoubtedly the hardest physically and mentally to play, and our numbers and any poll you care to mention bear that out. <br>
And even if AE is slightly unbalanced- A fact I disagree with strongly, due to risk v reward and the sheer boredom factor (ie, more can do it than practice it, do it since the nerf or have the system for it) but will concede for this point alone-<br>
<br>
If we were overpowered, as we were during the EN phase, when there were a crapload of Bards compared to now, why aren't we still Sony? Why have our numbers been drastically reduced since then? Didn't you do enough of a number on us with that?<br>
Why aren't people playing Bards Sony?<br>
Because we are HARD to play well- we are a hell of alot of work for a game, ask about anyone who has a bard alt, why they don't play their bard, and the answer is almost invariably the same "Bards are too much work"<br>
We deserve a benefit from that, if nothing else. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wildcarddesigns.com/images/edsigb.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
